Q18: 4th Amendment protects against unwarranted, & unreasonable search & seizure of a person’s property, even electronic.  I refuse to wave these rights under some notion of "general security".  The 4th originally enforced the idea that each man’s home is his castle, secure from unreasonable search & seizure by the government.  It is the basis of the law regarding search warrants, stop-and-frisk, wiretaps, and other forms of surveillance, as well as general respect for the "rule of law" on which our democratic system depends.  Unlike the Foreign Intelligence Surveillance Act (FISA) that targets foreign nationals and governments, FBI general counsel Andrew Weissmann, publicly expressed that the bureau wants to wiretap all forms of internet communication in real time. Applications such as Skype, Gmail, and Dropbox were specifically named, spying on American citizens under the Communications Assistance for Law Enforcement Act (CALEA), passed under Clinton.  It wasn't OK under Clinton or Bush; It isn't OK under Obama.
